name: Seattle Terrors Boos and Booze Haunted Pub Crawl
description:
Come on our Haunted Pub Crawl tour presented by US Ghost Adventures!
Enjoy local spirits while hearing about the city's haunted Spirits and wandering the haunted streets of Seattle. Join us on the new Boos and Booze Haunted Pub Crawl and visit the city's historic haunts and ghostly pubs to enjoy booze and boos at some of Seattle's most infamous paranormal and tipsy hotspots.

brand.name: Seattle Terrors By Us Ghost Adv...

review.name: Great for groups
review.reviewBody: We went out for my birthday with a huge group. Noah was our guide and did an excellent job helping us understand seattles haunted history. I would recommend for large groups or special events.

review.name: A must do in Seattle.
review.reviewBody: The tour was very informative and fun. Our tour guide was very knowledgeable, relatable and had incredible story telling skills. We visited Seattle for four days and this was the best activity of the entire trip! Highly recommend for a fun evening.

review.name: Seattle terror pub crawl
review.reviewBody: We had an amazing time on our tour. We ended up being the only people who booked so my family and I had a private tour. We were able to use the EMF detector the whole time and heard plenty of history from Michael. Michael was a great guide with so much knowledge on Seattle and just a cool person in general that we were able to converse with. The tour exceeded our expectations, would recommend to anyone visiting.

review.name: Good way to kill a couple hours in Seattle
review.reviewBody:
It was a cute way to see some of Seattle, hear a bit of history and have a couple drinks.
You are taken to 4 different bars or pubs around old Seattle and get to hear spooky true tales of Seattle's past.

review.name: An evening of fun, chilling tales, and Seattle history.
review.reviewBody: Michael was running a bit late, but sent a message to let us know. Once he arrived however, we were not disappointed! Michael was so knowledgeable, kind, and a joy to wander the downtown core with! His storytelling was on point and we loved that he included the background of the Salish peoples in his tales. It was honestly one of the best evenings had in a long time. Our group was fab and we walked away with new friends.

review.name: Misleading and Uninformed Tour
review.reviewBody: Lots of irrelevant, inappropriate opinionated statements by Noah the tour guide. Price of “drinking tickets” vs “non-drinking tickets” was misleading. No drinks were included in the tour. Last location was closed for a private event.

itemListElement.name: Roasted in Seattle Bean to Cup Coffee Tour

name: Roasted in Seattle Bean to Cup Coffee Tour
description: Delve deep into the heart of Seattle's renowned coffee culture on this bean-to-cup coffee tour, crafted especially for aficionados of the rich aromas and tantalizing flavors of the coffee world, which is alive and thriving on the bustling streets of Seattle. Let your senses be tantalized by the roasting beans, aromatic brews, and picturesque landscapes that define this vibrant city's coffee scene.

brand.name: Seattle Terrors By Us Ghost Adv...

itemListElement.name: Day Private Snoqualmie Falls & Woodinville Wine Tour from Seattle

name: Day Private Snoqualmie Falls & Woodinville Wine Tour from Seattle
description:
Embark on this Private Snoqualmie Falls and Woodinville Wine Tour and indulge your senses in the heart of USA's renowned wine country!

Your day begins with a personalized, chauffeur-driven journey through the stunning Woodinville region, setting the scene for an unforgettable adventure.

As you traverse the picturesque landscape, you'll have the opportunity to visit two wineries - Goose Ridge Woodinville Tasting Room and Ste. Michelle Winery - each with its own unique charm and distinctive wines. 

Expert sommeliers and winemakers will guide you through tastings of exceptional wines, sharing their deep knowledge and passion for winemaking. 

Enjoy a delightful traditional lunch, paired with local specialties, perfectly complementing the wines you've tasted throughout the day.

Don't miss the opportunity to create lasting memories on this Private Snoqualmie Falls and Woodinville Wine Tour, escaping the hustle for a day of indulgence and appreciation of USA's vinicultural heritage.

itemListElement.name: Seattle's Walking Cannabis Tour By Junket

name: Seattle's Walking Cannabis Tour By Junket
description:
Come on our Cannabis Walking Tour presented by Junket!
Thanks to some of the most expertly cultivated genetics, Seattle's producers are leading the cannabis industry and offering premium product to some of the country's most educated consumers. Travelers who are merely looking to purchase an eighth or two to keep them content while they explore the city are rarely aware of the lengthy history of Seattle's cannabis industry, despite the fact that cannabis has changed throughout time. You will have a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to learn what makes Seattle's cannabis so unique and why residents are pleased to having founded one of the nation's most successful industries on this tour. This tour will provide you an insightful introduction to Seattle's cannabis culture, whether you're "highly experienced" or a cannabis newbie. Light up now, grab a snack, and take in the sights of "The Emerald City."

review.name: So much fun on a Fri 13!
review.reviewBody: Michael was an excellent tour guide for me and my friends for my birthday! He’s so knowledgeable and we all became friends even. 10/10 recommend!

review.name: Definitely give this a shot
review.reviewBody: This tour was great!  My friends and I were in from out of town, and knew very little about Seattle.  Dakota was our guide, and was great!  She was very knowledgeable, personable, and fun.  Very interesting stories, as well as learning some history about Seattle.  We stopped at a bunch of bars with some great drinks throughout the tour.  I would highly recommend this tour, we all had a blast!

review.name: A good night out
review.reviewBody: Tour was fun and I learned some new bits of Seattle history, even with it not being my first Seattle ghost tour. It never felt rushed even with a fairly large group.

review.name: Boos and Booze
review.reviewBody: Enjoyed walking around the area of Seattle leaning the history of several different places while stopping for drinks. Very knowledgeable guide.

review.name: Great tour! Lots of fun!
review.reviewBody: Had a really great time!! The guide was engaging and the vibes were there! The sites we went to were very interesting, I especially enjoyed the Ted buddy intersection!

review.name: Booze tour
review.reviewBody: Ken was great, informative, funny, upbeat, and cool! We got to see things we probably wouldn’t have normally looked for

review.name: Great Seattle History
review.reviewBody: It was a beautiful evening! Our tour guide was awesome! Ended the evening discussing Seattles history and great conversations!  The tour took us through places we wouldn’t have otherwise seen. Would definitely recommend!

review.name: Boos & Brews experience…Michael was fabulous!!!
review.reviewBody: Fabulous tour of the boos and brews of Seattle.  Michael had lots of interesting & fascinating stories of Seattle to share with us!

review.name: They canceled our tour and now we have to try and get our money back.  The night before the tour let us know canceled.
review.reviewBody: The night before the tour they let us know the tour was canceled. We were very disappointed. They said we hot get money back

review.name: Don’t let them steal your money.
review.reviewBody: Bought two tickets through viator/trip advisor. Supposed to meet at 1416 first ave at 5:30. We got there at 5:00 and stayed until 6:10. No one showed up. Called viator to ask what the deal was they gave us the local office number. 1-844-757-5657. Called them. Everyone was unprofessional and kept saying, “we have to call the tour guide to see what really happened,” Like we missed the guide or something. (We did not, I was at the bar talking to the bar tender who knew the tour guides and said they haven’t seen them. He even went out to check). The dude on the phone for the local office took my name and number and said he only had one phone line to use so he had to hang up with me to try and call their tour guide. (He doesn’t have a cell phone?) So he hung up on me and never called back and I never got a refund.  Out $74 dollars. Viator and Seattle Terrors are both scams as far as I’m concerned. Horrible

itemListElement.name: Painting the Rainbow LGBTQ History Tour By Junket

name: Painting the Rainbow LGBTQ History Tour By Junket
description:
Come on our Walking Tour presented by Junket!
The LGBTQ community has long considered Seattle to be a mecca, with its Capitol Hill area being one of the most accepting in the nation. Come us on this tour as we examine six Capitol Hill landmarks and their significance to the LGBTQ community.

We hope you'll enjoy the Capitol Hill LGBTQ+ neighborhood in Seattle, which has something for everyone, from distinctive rainbow pride t-shirts to elixirs for a cause, stiff drinks in a dimly lit bar, a sugar high reminiscent of your childhood, and hours of dancing with your friends, powered by liquid bravery.

brand.name: Seattle Terrors By Us Ghost Adv...

itemListElement.name: Meet Me at the Market Food Tour

name: Meet Me at the Market Food Tour
description:
Welcome to the most fun and low-stress way to explore Pike Place Market! This tour is perfect for anyone interested in the market's diverse culinary offerings, as well as those who wish to learn about its rich culture and history. 

We keep it short, sweet and to-the-point. The tour lasts for 1 hour and 15 minutes and all food tastings are included in the price of admission. With us you'll get an idea of where to start and what to look out for when exploring the market on your own.

This tour offers food, flavor and so much more! You'll visit some of the most iconic spots on the West Coast, like the salmon-tossing fishmongers and the oldest Starbucks location. You’ll also explore some of the market’s lesser-known corridors as your guide shares interesting stories of those who have enriched the market with culture and identity.

A typical tasting menu includes smoked salmon, tea, chocolate, soup and baked goods.

review.name: Pike Place Tour Top Notch
review.reviewBody:
My daughter and I had a fabulous time. This tour made our trip to Seattle for several reasons.
1. This was the only food tour that accommodated my daughter’s lightweight wheelchair.
2. Our guide, Will, was knowledgeable, funny, and took care of all the people on this tour - I have a food allergy and Will arranged alternatives for me so that I also could enjoy the food too.
3. Group size was small - 8 people and therefore very personable.
4. Background stories about each food or shop added uniqueness and enjoyable information.
5. Pace was perfect. We didn’t stop and stand around for long periods of time or felt rushed to get to the next stop.

And most of all the food was delicious.
I would highly recommend this tour! Thanks, Will for a fun noontime experience.

review.name: Market Tastiness!
review.reviewBody: Wil is a great guide! He is very knowledge about the Market and he uses food to connect you to the Market! What a great introduction to both the Market and where you might like to eat! Definitely take this tour!

review.name: A Great Time and Great Food
review.reviewBody:
Will was amazing! His laid back attitude made him very comfortable to chat with as we walked, and our tour had a leisurely pace that was just perfect for the rainy Sunday. Everyone we spoke with was wonderful, all ready to share information about what they had to offer, and as a bonus, Will provided historical facts about the market itself. Every single thing we ate was PHENOMENAL -- the chai from Aditi, the perfectly ripe persimmons, the lamb stew from Turkish Delight... keep in mind that many places can pack to travel or will ship to you, so don't be shy about asking for business cards or websites. 

We absolutely recommend this tour! Thank you so much!

review.name: Fun and unique snacks in Pike Place
review.reviewBody: Will was friendly and knowledgeable about the local vendors. The food stops were fun and unique. We enjoyed the tour and places to try for future meals.

review.name: Snacks tour at Pike Place Market
review.reviewBody: During this tour I learned a lot about this emblematic place of Seattle. Will my guide is knowledgeable, nice and very helpful. I made me taste several delicious things like this amazing pink guava by Rachel ginger beer or a chowder from Pike place chowder. I tasted a croissant with a delicious apricot jam and others things. I had definitely a nice tour. I highly recommend this tour.

itemListElement.name: Downtown Seattle Foodie Tour By Junket

name: Downtown Seattle Foodie Tour By Junket
description:
Come on our Flavorful Food Tour presented by Junket!
With its combination of fresh seafood and mountain techniques, Seattle nearly has its own cuisine. Every culture represented in Seattle has brought their own traditional foods with them. This tour offers everything, with a little history thrown in, from sushi rolls to mac & cheese, from chocolates to French pastries. Join us on this delicious savory gastronomic tour to fill both your stomach and your mind.

brand.name: Seattle Terrors By Us Ghost Adv...

itemListElement.name: Pike Place Market Gourmet Food Tour

name: Pike Place Market Gourmet Food Tour
description:
Does Seattle have its own unique culinary “style?” 

Dine with us on this Gourmet Restaurant Tour through Pike Place Market and come away with a deeper understanding of Northwest Culture. 

This tour includes a full meal of tastings from Downtown Seattle’s best restaurants. Most of the tour is spent sitting inside, enjoying classic dishes with a Seattle twist.

Additionally, this tour crawls through the corridors of Pike Place Market, providing you with an insider view of day-to-day Market Life. 

You will learn about the culinary scene in Seattle and come to understand the city's role in bringing fusion and artisan culture to the mainstream. 

You’ll also discover why Seattle is home to the “BEST version of your favorite food!”

The itinerary changes from one tour to the next, but a typical tasting menu includes seafood, meats, comfort foods, and dessert. We carter to all dietary restrictions. 

Alcoholic/non-alcoholic beverages are available for purchase from the restaurants.

review.name: Great!
review.reviewBody: Will was great, friendly and knowledgeable about the food and wines, and also the new and interesting restaurants around, and he was accommodating to our tastes. There were only 3 of us, so it was as less ‘tour-y’ and more hang out and eat amazing food with a local. Recommend this tour.

review.name: Excellent tour guide
review.reviewBody: Will is very knowledgeable, accommodating and attentive. Highly recommend any of his tours to locals and tourists alike. We will be coming back to Will for his chocolate tour.

review.name: Fun
review.reviewBody: Will was a great guide, warmly greeted at each restaurant. He filled us in on the history of  the restaurants and pike place market. Great variety of food tastings. Appreciated Will’s friendly nature.

review.name: Look for a more historical food tour of Seattle
review.reviewBody:
The tour guide Will is a really sweet guy. He seems to know a decent amount of knowledge about food but the problem I have with this tour is that we learned nothing. There seemed to be no historical relevance to the food locations we had tastings for and if there was we weren't told about them. All we  did was walk to about 5 locations and taste something they sell. 

I've been on a handful of food tours around the US and I would not recommend this tour unless they switched it up and added some food locations that make Seattle what it's known for. From this tour I have no idea.

review.name: Great tour, wonderful guide
review.reviewBody: This was the second tour I went on with Jade and she was wonderful both times.  It was like being shown around the city by a friend.  She is a trained pastry chef with a minor in chocolate! and knows all about the food scene in Seattle.  We tried lots of different and interesting things, heard a lot about the businesses we visited and had a great time.  I would highly recommend this tour and would have booked more with this company after talking to her if I'd had the time.

review.name: Great time discovering new downtown restaurants
review.reviewBody: We had a great time visiting new restaurants in and around Pike Place Market.  Our guide was knowledgeable and fun and we discovering new restaurants that we may not have visited before.  Highly recommend.

review.name: Great food and great tour
review.reviewBody: Ivy did a great job and the food was great. We learned a lot about the market and the history of the city.

review.name: A Must Do
review.reviewBody: Ivy was awesome! She was very knowledgeable and we got to sample lots of great food. This is a great way to sample the local cuisine!!

review.name: 10/10 - Best Comfort Food
review.reviewBody: Jade gave a great comfort food tour of Seattle! Make sure you go hungry because there’s plenty of food to eat! Our favorites were the Jamaican meat pie and the Turkish lamb stews. Absolutely delish!

review.name: Good food in comfortable places
review.reviewBody: Good food in 6 comfortable places. Would have enjoyed more with fewer places and more discussion of places we didn't get to.

itemListElement.name: Coffee & Food Tastings at Pike Place Market

name: Coffee & Food Tastings at Pike Place Market
description:
Embark on a culinary adventure through the heart of Seattle's vibrant Pike Place Market. Join a chef guided walking tasting tour that promises to delight your palate with delicious food and coffee samples. We will eat donuts, salmon, cheesecake and more. Of course, there are stops at the Gum Wall Starbucks and the flying fish market.
Your gastronomic exploration includes the aromatic allure of Seattle's world-renowned coffee culture. Sip on a freshly brewed cup of rich, locally sourced coffee as you learn about the city's love affair with the bean.

Thoughtful Chef Tours is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market Preservation and Development Authority (PDA) to operate in the Pike Place market Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting paid tours within its properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: I had an absolute blast!
review.reviewBody: Carolyn was so accommodating and friendly. She was knowledgeable about the food, the history, and the culture of Seattle and it was lovely to chat with her during the tour. There was a variety of food to try and everything was amazing. Highly, highly recommend!

review.name: Taste of Pike Place
review.reviewBody:
This tour was fantastic - full of historical insights about Seattle, the region, and the Pike Place Market. We lucked out and got Carolyn all to ourselves! She shared some of the complexities of Seattle’s history including the displacement of indigenous people and the internment of Japanese families during WWII. The focus on local merchants and the tastes were also marvelous. 

Along the way we enjoyed a delightful chocolate croissant, an excellent grilled cheese sandwich, some Washington state apples, and some smoked garlic pepper salmon. 

Lou at Hellenika Creamery gave us a rundown of the company’s history and the chemistry behind their amazing gelato! Try the Seattle Fog (Earl Grey flavored) and the 7th Inning Stretch (think CrackerJack caramel corn). 

Early in our tour Carolyn mentioned Indi Chocolate and the owner, Erin’s commitment to building relationships with the cacao farmers. We shared our interest in the chocolate making process so later in the tour Carolyn took us by Indi. We enjoyed a sample of their hand lotion which Erin says is a favorite among the fish market guys on date nights! The scent of the lotion was amazing. 

For the coffee fans, we sampled a latte at Victrola, a mocha at Chocolate and Ice Cream Delight, and a French press at Storyville. All were quite good - and we don’t usually prefer coffee!

It’s clear that Carolyn has a deep appreciation and affection for the Market and its people. Many of the merchants know her by name and wave or call out a happy greeting. This tour is a great way to enjoy the stories and tastes of the Pike Place Market!

review.name: A must do!
review.reviewBody: This tour was amazing! Our guide was wonderful and very knowledgeable about the market. I have never been to Seattle, but my husband and mother-in-law are from the area, and they said they even learned something new. It was a memorable experience and I would highly recommend it!!!

review.name: The best food and coffee tour in Pike’s
review.reviewBody: Carolyn was fabulous!! We absolutely loved her! She’s so charismatic, warm and fun. The tour pace was perfect and every food bite and coffee was so incredibly good.

review.name: Coffee + Food tour with Carolyn
review.reviewBody: We had a great time! Carolyn is very knowledgeable about the history of the area and the food was amazing. Highly recommend!

review.name: Great experience
review.reviewBody: Great experience! We enjoyed this tour very much, Carolyn shared lots of great information! Highly recommend!!!!!!!

review.name: I’ll be back!
review.reviewBody: Chef Carolyn was amazing and very knowledgeable of the areas history. The coffee and food were all amazing. I’m a very picky eater and I loved all the food. I highly recommend! I will be coming back to Seattle next month with family and friends and we will most definitely be booking a tour with Carolyn.

review.name: Coffee and Brunch Tour with Carolyn
review.reviewBody: Carolyn was awesome! Our family had the best time on the coffee and brunch tour. Learned so many fun historical facts and got to taste a little bit of everything. Highly recommend!!

review.name: Sign up NOW!
review.reviewBody: Don't miss this one - an insider's look at Pike's Place Market with history, storytelling and warm welcomes from stalls/vendors. Everyone knows and loves Carolyn. She gave us a wonderful two+ hours of insights, little known facts and tastes of some of the best the Market has to offer. Highly recommend!

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: We enjoyed the tour of Pike Place market with interesting stories as well as sampling coffee, pastries, and desserts at various spots around the market. Tour guide was friendly, knowledgeable, and had enough material for the entire 2 hour experience.

itemListElement.name: Seattle Downtown Quest: Self-Guided History Adventure

name: Seattle Downtown Quest: Self-Guided History Adventure
description:
Step into Seattle’s past and uncover the hidden stories that shaped the city through an interactive walking quest. Explore downtown like never before as you dive into tales of fire, fortune, and underground secrets.

Guided by your smartphone, you’ll solve 10 clever puzzles while discovering landmarks tied to the Klondike Gold Rush, the Great Seattle Fire, and the mysterious Seattle Underground. Every challenge unlocks a new layer of history, guiding you seamlessly through historic streets, squares, and famous sites. No map, GPS, or guide needed—just solve the clues and reveal the secrets.

What makes this tour unique?
It’s a story-driven adventure that combines Seattle’s colorful history with interactive discovery, giving you the freedom to explore at your own pace while bringing the past vividly to life.

Perfect for curious travelers, families, friends, and history buffs who love solving puzzles and uncovering hidden gems.

review.name: Fun, Fun, Fun!
review.reviewBody: Was so much fun.  We learned a lot about Seattle and got in some good exercise.  Time went so fast.  Would do this in other cities.

review.name: Fun family time.
review.reviewBody: Fun little adventure in and around downtown Seattle. Completed this past weekend with our family of 6. Great clues and educational too. It took us a little more than an hour to do.

review.name: Take a mirror to read some of the clues.
review.reviewBody:
"It could be more engaging," said the 14 year old. 
Online support staff was great unraveling an error in logon info, but it took1.5 hours to do so.
You need to download an app, so only those in your group with an app  should need to pay. For 1 adult and 4 kids, $45, was way too much and  we quit after 5 of the 10 clues. 
We liked the starting point. A national park in downtown Seattle! They offer a free 1 hour wallking tour.
We were disappointed.

review.name: A MUST Do
review.reviewBody: How fun this was! I truly thought this was going to be more like an escape room, and while there were some elements of that puzzle-like approach, this was an incredibly fun way to learn about the city, do some exploring, and take a very nice walk. Be prepared for the weather of course as Seattle is very rainy. This is easily friendly for the whole family or something to do solo as you're walking around the city and viewing various historical sites, interacting with the different locations you encounter in one way or another. One of the stops along the way is the Smith Tower and be sure to budget time to stop and take the tour! We were lucky enough to catch the end of their weekend brunch. I am so glad we did this as it is such an amazing way to have fun, see the city, and be outdoors without spending an arm and a leg.

review.name: Fun Seattle Historical Walking Tour.
review.reviewBody: We had a blast! It was fun finding the clues and walking through the city. We learned some interesting facts about Seattle’s history during the early years. We had a few glitches initially but seemed more user error. I would recommend this walking tour.

review.name: Amazing
review.reviewBody: This is amazing. Got to see some things I didn’t know and learn the history. Awesome idea for a date night.

review.name: Seattle Scavenger Hunt
review.reviewBody: This was a fun and inexpensive way to experience the city and learn more about Seattle history along the way. A few stops were more challenging then others and required the use of extra clues, but we enjoyed the adventure.

review.name: Fun and exciting..

itemListElement.name: Mad Scientist Cocktail and Mocktail Lab

name: Mad Scientist Cocktail and Mocktail Lab
description:
lab·​o·​ra·​to·​ry | \ ˈla-b(ə-)rə-ˌtȯr-ē A place providing opportunity for experimentation, observation, or practice in a field of study.

This is an ever-changing and high concept cocktail workshop (aka. laboratory) for those with 0 to 100 levels of experience. Unconventional, not a class; learn through experimentation! You get to take risks in this lab that you wouldn't normally take at home with hundreds of ingredients at your fingertips. Tools include smoking gun, test tubes, shaker sets, etc.

It is my goal as your host to work with each of you and fine-tune each event to fit your individual mixology goals. By design, any awkwardness and negative judgement is kicked out the door in order for the madness to ensue!

review.name: 5 Stars – A Must-Do in Seattle!
review.reviewBody:
I can’t recommend the Mad Scientist Cocktail and Mocktail Lab enough — what an absolute blast. From the second we walked in, the vibe was fun, light, and totally welcoming. Jen, our host, was incredibly knowledgeable but kept things relaxed and playful the whole time. You could tell she knew her stuff, but she made sure the focus stayed on creativity and enjoyment, not rules or perfection.

What I loved most was how everyone participated — whether you’re a mixology nerd or just curious, there was zero pressure and no wrong way to experiment. The small, intimate group made it easy to connect and share creations, and somehow, everyone just fit. It felt like a perfect mix of structure and freedom, and by the end, we were all laughing and sipping drinks we’d never think to make on our own.

A totally unique and memorable experience. If you’re in Seattle, go. Whether you drink alcohol or not, you’ll walk out with a smile.

review.name: Must try!
review.reviewBody: Was super fun, involved, and worth the time and cost!  The amount of ingredients and choices made it super exciting to try crazy new drinks!

review.name: True Experimentation Experience
review.reviewBody: We went for a friend's birthday and had a fantastic time! The lab is well-stocked and the lead scientist is knowledgeable and helpful. She started with a tour of the lab and how she organized ingredients and then we were left to our own devices (except for the smoker). Everyone in my group had a fun time deciding what ingredients to mix and match and try. Some of our concoctions tasted professional, some tasted toxic, but we enjoyed bringing to life what our imaginations thought up and assigning punny names for each drink. I would highly recommend to any friend group that enjoys drinking, laughing, and experimenting together!

review.name: The eye opening drink experience
review.reviewBody: How do you make something as old as cocktail creations so fresh and new! A fantastic usage of space with an even superior sense for human, this experience is one and a million. I learned more about what kind of spirits I’m fond of, made a new friend, and learned most importantly what doesn’t blend well with what I like.

review.name: A must for a creative date night!
review.reviewBody: We had such a great time last night creating fun cocktails.  It’s such a cute, quaint environment with everything available for you to experiment with. Our hostess was knowledgeable, fun and gave us the latitude to pretty much make anything that we wanted to with what was there. It was a great date night!

review.name: Best Group Activity
review.reviewBody: What a fun family and friends group experience!  I loved experimenting with Mocktail recipes but the rest of our group had fun pretending to be bartenders concocting cocktails.  We were an intergenerational group of all ages and it is hard to find an activity in the heart of Seattle that gives everyone a great time and still allows for conversation and collaboration.  Jen stocks the bar well and there is no recipe she can't help create with a little imagination. I highly recommend this fun laboratory in a great neighborhood.

review.name: Great time
review.reviewBody: We had a great time and look forward to doing it again! There was quite the bevy of mixology options that we did not get a chance to try everything out in time. :)

review.name: a great date idea to break the norm
review.reviewBody:
This is a great place to go for a fun and creative experience. The lab is designed for people of all experience levels, so you don't need to be a mixologist to have a good time. There are hundreds of ingredients and tools available for use, so you can create whatever you can imagine. The atmosphere is fun and relaxed, and the owner, Jen, is knowledgeable and helpful. She is always happy to answer questions and offer suggestions.

I highly recommend the Mad Scientist Cocktail and Mocktail Lab for anyone looking for a unique and enjoyable experience. It is a great place to go for a date night, a group outing, or just a fun night out with friends.

review.name: Fun time experimenting with cocktails.
review.reviewBody:
First, the space the workshop was in was incredible. It was upstairs in a loft in an old brick building just up on Capitol Hill from the Convention Center. It felt like a hidden speakeasy. There were loads of interesting curios around the lab: an old phone (that worked), books with secret compartments, a fortune cookie dispenser with adults-only fortunes, a bar globe, among other fascinating artifacts. The host spent the first 10 or 15 minutes explaining how things work and emphasized that it was not a mixology class, but rather a laboratory where all the time was yours to spend experimenting. There seemed to be dozens of different types and brands of alcohol and hundreds of different things you could add to the alcohol: sweet syrups, flavored bitters, ice, smoke, fruit, dried spices, etc. For my first cocktail, I decided to keep it simple and create a rum old-fashioned with some spice. The drinks that followed were much more experimental, using things like avocado powder, glitter, charred salt, smoke, chocolate, and rosemary. Altogether, I made four drinks in the two hours and sampled other people's drinks as well. The host and her assistant were super friendly and answered any questions I asked them.

I highly recommend this activity for both groups, singles and for a good date night.

review.name: Mad Scientist Cocktail and Mocktail Lab
review.reviewBody: The Mad Scientist Cocktail and Mocktail Lab was an experience like no other.  From the moment you step through the doors and into the lab there is a level of sophistication and creativity.  I do not want to give too much away, but the lab experience is the opportunity to unleash your creativity and experiment with different flavor combinations. From smoky mezcal infusions to tangy citrus blends, the possibilities are endless. With a vast array of ingredients at your disposal, you're free to let your imagination run wild and create drinks that are as unique as you are. Jen does a great welcoming her guests in and I feel it is a must go and visit if you are in town.  Additionally, to have the opportunity to even mix, mingle, and connect with people is fanatic especially since Seattle has this misconception of an introvert town.

name: Seattle Vacation Home: Berlin Wall - Sparkling Clean in PRIME location! Decks
description:
Welcome to “The Berlin Wall”! You will feel right at home in this 3 bedroom townhome with *fantastic* amenities and convenient location!

Each of our homes has been decorated to pay homage to a meaningful facet of our lives. This home ("The Berlin Wall") pays homage to a city in which Lynne lived for a year!

~ What You Will Love ~
*High-end kitchen and bathrooms
*Open concept floor-thru living area
*Full floor master suite w/ jetted tub & view deck
*Garage
*Centrally located near top dining, parks, hiking & day spas
*Seattle Vacation Home Hospitality

KITCHEN / DINING
This open concept space has a modern kitchen with granite counter tops and stainless steel appliances. This flows directly to the dining area which includes 3 stools at the breakfast counter, and a dining table that seats 8 and expands to accommodate more.

LIVING ROOM
The living areas are spread over three levels. The entry level is the main living area furnished with plenty of seating, DirectTV, and a DVD player.

There is a queen size sleeper sofa (with highest end sofa bed mattress on the market) for larger groups. Enjoy our collection of games (Scrabble, cards, etc.) in front of the gas fireplace.

LAUNDRY
There is a full-size washer dryer available for your use.

BEDROOMS
Bedroom 1: Located up one flight of stairs (same level as BR 2) and has a king bed and large closet.

Bedroom 2: Located up one flight of stairs (same level as BR 1) and offers great flexibility. It is furnished with three beds, including a twin over full bunk bed (solid and sturdy --- not just for kids!) and a standalone twin bed.

Bedroom 3: Located on the top (third) floor, you arrive at the full-floor master suite. This room has a king bed and a window air conditioning unit (note that this is the only bedroom with air conditioning, which is a real rarity in Seattle). There is a large balcony with views overlooking Madison Valley. On a clear day, enjoy the Cascade Mountain Range in the distance. The master suite also has a large walk-in closet and a 5-piece spa bathroom with *jetted* soaking tub, his and her sinks, and a toilet separated by a door for privacy.

BATHROOMS
Bathroom 1: Powder room (half bath) located on first floor.
Bathroom 2: BR 1 & BR 2 share a nearby full bathroom with dual sinks separated from the bathtub and toilet for added privacy.
Bathroom 3: The master bath has a 5-piece spa bathroom with *jetted* soaking tub, his and her sinks, and a toilet separated by a door for privacy.

ACCESS
Access to the home is provided without a cumbersome lock box or key exchange. Instead, you will choose a 4 digit code, and the electronic lock to the home will be programmed to work for the duration of your stay.

You will have access to the entire home, including parking for one car in the attached garage (and plentiful free street parking for additional vehicles). The garage is located one level below the "entry level" noted above.

AIR CONDITIONING
Air conditioning is a real rarity in Seattle.  This home does not have central A/C, but does have a small window unit air conditioner in the kitchen area window and in the master bedroom on the top floor. 

INTERACTION WITH GUESTS
Your hosts live just down the block. We are here to welcome you and help you with any of your needs during your stay. We are happy to offer you advice for sightseeing, restaurant recommendations, and even some budget saving tips and coupons.

Guests will receive, in advance, our comprehensive homemade visitors' guide to Seattle, packed with our personal recommendations for dining, activities, and much more.

OTHER THINGS TO NOTE
Do you plan to cook during your stay? By special advanced arrangement (depending on availability), we will fulfill your grocery list and have your home stocked for your arrival.

Is your group larger than this home will accommodate? We can host up to *388* guests across our portfolio of 30+ homes --- with all homes located in close proximity to each other!

Seattle Vacation Home has 1 through 8 bedrooms homes, and everything in between. All of our homes are in a compact area... perfect for large groups, wedding guests, reunions, corporate retreats, etc.

All homes are fully furnished to high standards and feature all the comforts our guests have come to love.

THE NEIGHBORHOOD
This home is central to everything Madison Valley has to offer: great restaurants, parks, hiking, supermarkets, day spas, and more. Your hosts made Madison Valley their home when first settling in Seattle... and haven't looked back since.

We love walking the streets of this neighborhood and we will gladly suggest fun walks depending on your interests. Stroll to the beach at Madison Park. Walk by multi-million dollar estates. Discover hidden neighborhood gems such as the farmhouse with horses in the yard and the home that doubles as an eclectic art studio and antique truck gallery. Take a walk through the fabled Arboretum to Lake Washington.
